type: FIGHTER
benefit: "In addition to the standard single extra attack you get with an off-hand weapon, you get a second attack with it, albeit at a - 5 penalty (see Table 8-10, page 160)."
special: "A fighter may select Improved Two-Weapon Fighting as one of his fighter bonus feats. \n\nA 6th-level ranger who has chosen the two-weapon combat style is treated as having Improved Two-Weapon Fighting, even if he does not have the prerequisites for it, but only when he is wearing light or no armor (see page 48)."
normal: "Without this feat, you can only get a single extra attack with an off-hand weapon."
prerequisites: "Dex 17, Two-Weapon Fighting, base attack bonus +6."
